author: Forrest Hanson For Dailymail.Com
title: Texas fraternities suspended after sorority death | Daily Mail Online
text: Four Texas State University fraternities are suspended for 'alcohol violations' after sorority member was dragged 500ft to her death under a party bus Four fraternities at Texas State University suspended for 'alcohol-related policy violations' Body of Jordin Taylor, 20, was found morning following an off-campus event She had been dragged 500 ft by a bus used to haul inner-tubers to and from river Officials did not directly connect suspensions to death but said violations took place at 'off-campus social event' the night before her body was found Published: 00:42 GMT, 1 February 2017 | Updated: 03:55 GMT, 1 February 2017 24 shares
